風通し
かぜとおし【風通し】 ﾛｰﾏ(kazetooshi)
1 〔風が通ること〕 ventilation.
▲風通しがよい　be ⌐airy [well-ventilated]
・風通しが悪い　be ⌐airless [ill-ventilated, poorly ventilated, close, stuffy].
▲風通しの悪い　airless; ill-ventilated; poorly ventilated; close; stuffy
・夏服には風通しのよい素材を選びましょう.　For summer clothes, choose a fabric that ⌐lets in the cool air [breathes well].
▲少し植木を切って庭の風通しをよくした.　I pruned the trees to let more air into the garden.
2 〔組織などの開放性〕 openness; an open atmosphere.
▲執行部が若返って党内の風通しがよくなった.　With a new, younger leadership, the party took on a fresher, more open feel.
▲従業員の発言の機会をふやして社内の風通しをよくしたい.　I would like to create a more open atmosphere in the company by giving employees a greater chance to have their say.
